<h1>Problem 422 - 2002 France TST, P3 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(n\) be a positive integer and let \((a_1, a_2, \dots , a_{2n})\) be a permutation of \(1, 2, \dots , 2n\) such that the numbers \(\lvert a_{i + 1} - a_i \rvert\) are pairwise distinct for \(i = 1, 2, \dots , 2n-1.\) Prove that \(\{ a_2, a_4, \dots , a_{2n} \}  = \{1, 2, \dots , n\}\) if and only if \(a_1 - a_{2n} = n.\)</p>
